author: Rick Peterson Jr.
title: Washburn soccer drops 1-0 decision to Northeastern State
text:
Washburn soccer drops 1-0 decision to Northeastern State Early goal lifts RiverHawks By Rick Peterson Jr. richard.peterson@cjonline.com 
Two days after the Washburn soccer team struggled to generate any momentum against Central Oklahoma, the Ichabods kept Northeastern State in check Sunday and managed to string together opportunities. 
The only thing missing for the Ichabods was a goal, with the RiverHawks blanking Washburn 1-0 at Yager Stadium. 
NSU’s Jennifer Cudjoe scored the lone goal, deking a WU defender before firing in a shot from about 20 yards out in the seventh minute. 
Despite the loss, WU coach Chris Jones said he was pleased with the showing. 
“The attitude coming into the game felt a lot different than Friday,” Jones said. “They were up to the challenge and ready to play, which is good to see. 
“(Cudjoe) is a crafty player. It was a wonder goal that beat us. Then the second half, we put them under pressure. I don’t think they troubled us once the second half. I am really proud of the way we fought back in the second half. It was definitely a complete turnaround from Friday.” 
Washburn (2-6-2, 1-3-0 MIAA), put some pressure on the RiverHawks in the second half, outshooting Northeastern State 6-3. Jordan Woodruff posted the shutout for NSU (8-2, 3-1). 
“When we had the opportunities, we were right there, the ball just didn’t bounce the right way or we were one second too late or one second too early,” Jones said. “We’ll correct that.” 
Washburn put up seven shots, with Rachel Kuhlanek, Cadence Bourne and Morgan El-Attrache attempting two apiece. 
Kaitlin Minnich recorded two saves in goal for the Ichabods. 
Cudjoe’s goal was one of the few opportunities Washburn allowed, leaving Jones satisfied with WU’s defensive effort. 
“We high-pressured them and kept them basically in their half most of the game,” Jones said. “We were really organized defensively, and we were organized when we had the ball. It’s just finding that final decision.” 
Washburn will continue a four-game homestand against Missouri Western at 6 p.m. Friday. 
Northeastern State 1 0 — 1 
Washburn 0 0 — 0 
Northeastern State — Goal: Cudjoe. Shutout: Woodruff. 
Records — Northeastern State: 8-2, 3-1 MIAA. Washburn 2-6-2, 1-3 MIAA.
